  }, "A vector is a string of numbers treated as a single entity. For example, the four measurements of each iris flower mean we can represent the flower as a string of four numbers, say, (4.5, 2.3, 1.3, 0.3). The flower described by this vector has a sepal length of 4.5 cm, sepal width of 2.3 cm, petal length of 1.3 cm, and petal width of 0.3 cm. By grouping these measurements together, we can refer to them as a single entity."), mdx("li", {
